 4, 'num_reactions': 40, 'num_reposts': 4, 'post_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7037316554232909825/', 'posted': '2023-03-03 07:03:33', 'poster': {'first': 'Premkumar', 'headline': 'Reinventing the B2B sales with 3D Avatar', 'image_url': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQHCutswPiNIxQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1670561922817?e=1758153600&v=beta&t=Li4DXV1Bzq_PuQVSK-wMTGyo6j09USK6cjT58bEN9Ho', 'last': 'Jagadeesan', 'linkedin_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/premkumar-jagadeesan-538a7658', 'public_id': 'premkumar-jagadeesan-538a7658', 'urn': 'ACoAAAxCmnwBRsVWmVIxeUBoSlo33iq-9s8PRdY'}, 'poster_linkedin_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/premkumar-jagadeesan-538a7658', 'reshared': False, 'text': "Our team is proud to announce the launch of our newest software product, JSONStudio!\n\nAs a developer, I always wondered why most Online JSON tools do not have a simplified UI Design and an easy way to navigate the various features they offer.\n\nTherefore Our Team has decided to build an all-in-one new-generation free online tool that provides various exclusive features like ChatGPT text-to-JSON conversion, search history view, cloud storage, download, share and visualize JSON data in DB, grid, crack, and tree modes.\n\nWe're excited to share this product with our network and invite you to check it out for yourself and post your comments on ProductHunt.\n\nhttps://lnkd.in/geJ7g4QC\n\nhttps://jsonstudio.io/ \n\n#chatgpt #json #freetools #crack #visualization #conversion #csv #yaml #xml #cloudstorage #episyche", 'time': '2 years ago', 'urn': '7037316554232909825'}, {'attributes': [], 'images': [{'url': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5622AQE_-JG-u13YGw/feedshare-shrink_2048_1536/feedshare-shrink_2048_1536/0/1672119945600?e=1758153600&v=beta&t=f_kUruVbznROykhk6tl804MDznM5SypHqYa5GmB7u-0'}], 'num_comments': 0, 'num_likes': 2, 'num_reactions': 2, 'num_reposts': 5, 'post_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7013379387806937089/', 'posted': '2022-12-27 05:45:48', 'poster_linkedin_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/episyche', 'repost_stats': {'num_appreciations': 0, 'num_comments': 0, 'num_empathy': 0, 'num_interests': 0, 'num_likes': 7, 'num_maybe': 0, 'num_praises': 0, 'num_reactions': 7, 'num_reposts': 0}, 'repost_urn': '7013380135953326080', 'reposted': '2022-12-27 05:48:46', 'reshared': True, 'resharer_comment': "To Add Drag and Drop feature to your Next.js website, please read the below blog.\n\nhttps://lnkd.in/gH7fycxv\n\nPlease follow Episyche's Linkedin Page for more informative blogs.\n\nhttps://lnkd.in/gagWbuyE", 'text': 'Drag and Drop is a pointing device gesture in which the user selects a virtual object by "grabbing" it and dragging it to a different location. \n\nThe below blog explains how to add a Drag and Drop feature in the Next.js application using React DND.\n\nhttps://lnkd.in/g78KzDsv\n\n#nextjs #react #draganddrop #episyche #blog #blogpost #blogwriting #blogging #bloggingcommunity #bloggers #blogwebsite #blogposts #informationtechnology', 'time': '2 years ago', 'urn': '7013379387806937089'}, {'attributes': [], 'images': [{'url': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5622AQHQeHLgjagYxw/feedshare-shrink_2048_1536/feedshare-shrink_2048_1536/0/1671767801415?e=1758153600&v=beta&t=tdBsoIw18cWM7HGhWaVm1aKi6oKSmx3DGX8_FTV9A9c'}], 'num_comments': 0, 'num_likes': 4, 'num_reactions': 4, 'num_reposts': 5, 'post_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7011902379675590657/', 'posted': '2022-12-23 03:56:42', 'poster_linkedin_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/episyche', 'repost_stats': {'num_appreciations': 0, 'num_comments': 0, 'num_empathy': 0, 'num_interests': 0, 'num_likes': 4, 'num_maybe': 0, 'num_praises': 0, 'num_reactions': 4, 'num_reposts': 0}, 'repost_urn': '7011902680734318592', 'reposted': '2022-12-23 03:57:53', 'reshared': True, 'resharer_comment': 'Please check out our new blog on How to Integrate the Summernote WYSIWYG editor into Django.\n\nStay connected with us for more interesting blogs.', 'text': 'Suppose you are developing a blog application, in that writing every page directly using HTML, CSS and Javascript is a time-consuming activity and it will be difficult to manage the code if you have more pages. Therefore WYSIWYG editor is widely used to generate HTML pages dynamically and store them in the database. Once the content is stored in the Database you can easily read content using APIs and present it to the users. \n\nThe Below blog explains How to Integrate the Summernote WYSIWYG editor into Django.\n\nhttps://lnkd.in/gRsfizYP\n\n#django #djangorestframework #python #pythonprogramming #html #html5 #blog #blogwriting #episyche', 'time': '2 years ago', 'urn': '7011902379675590657'}, {'attributes': [], 'images': [{'url': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5622AQHzRAKkrSVy2w/feedshare-shrink_2048_1536/feedshare-shrink_2048_1536/0/1671687669526?e=1758153600&v=beta&t=QNoNS8KEwYIH_j7KL62_1eu4DLAq7fdmEotZjpX_8gg'}], 'num_comments': 0, 'num_likes': 5, 'num_reactions': 5, 'num_reposts': 7, 'post_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7011566285104836609/', 'posted': '2022-12-22 05:41:10', 'poster_linkedin_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/episyche', 'repost_stats': {'num_appreciations': 0, 'num_comments': 0, 'num_empathy': 0, 'num_interests': 0, 'num_likes': 8, 'num_maybe': 0, 'num_praises': 0, 'num_reactions': 8, 'num_reposts': 0}, 'repost_urn': '7011567457047887872', 'reposted': '2022-12-22 05:45:50', 'reshared': True, 'resharer_comment': 'Please check out our new blog on how to add search functionality to a react website using Elasticsearch.\n\nPlease follow our linked page for more interesting blogs.\n\nhttps://lnkd.in/gtfVkcwr\n\n#react #django #elasticsearch #searchinsidebar #episyche', 'text': 'Having a search feature on your website helps you increase the user engagement time on your site. And also it attracts more users to your site. Implementing the search features was a difficult and expensive job.\xa0 \n\nIn the below blog, we gonna explain How to add search functionality to a React and Django website using Elasticsearch?\n\n#elasticsearch #elasticsearchdeveloper #django #djangodeveloper #djangorestframework #searchinsidebar #search #searchengines #searchengineoptimization #searchengineresults #reactjs #react #searchconsole #searchresults', 'time': '2 years ago', 'urn': '7011566285104836609'}, {'attributes': [], 'images': [{'url': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D22AQE7AHrUwEcF6Q/feedshare-shrink_2048_1536/feedshare-shrink_2048_1536/0/1671549596202?e=1758153600&v=beta&t=8ZcuXWldDqESBbswOf1a3Yojbfn2Wk5zqUxcCI78zZQ'}], 'num_comments': 0, 'num_likes': 3, 'num_reactions': 3, 'num_reposts': 5, 'post_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7010987164293324800/', 'posted': '2022-12-20 15:19:57', 'poster_linkedin_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/episyche', 'repost_stats': {'num_appreciations': 0, 'num_comments': 0, 'num_empathy': 0, 'num_interests': 0, 'num_likes': 6, 'num_maybe': 0, 'num_praises': 0, 'num_reactions': 6, 'num_reposts': 0}, 'repost_urn': '7010987221193240576', 'reposted': '2022-12-20 15:20:11', 'reshared': True, 'text': 'Well-written API documentation saves a lot of time and effort spent by the developers to understand the API functionality and its underneath Database Model.\n\nSwagger Docs provides detailed information about functions, classes, return types, arguments, and more.\n\nIn the below blog, we have explained how to add API documentation to a Django Backend Application.\n\nhttps://lnkd.in/dysYaaM2\n\n#apidocumentation\xa0#swagger\xa0#django\xa0#djangorestframework\xa0#python\xa0#pythonprogramming\xa0#episyche\xa0#apidevelopment\xa0#documentation', 'time': '2 years ago', 'urn': '7010987164293324800'}, {'attributes': [], 'images': [], 'num_comments': 0, 'num_likes': 2, 'num_reactions': 2, 'num_reposts': 3,